<p>GDP growth: 10.9% GDP: $112bn (PPP: $159bn) Inflation: 6.1% Population: 32.8m GDP per head: $3,410 (PPP: $4,850)</p>

<p>Improving security will reinforce the virtuous cycle of rising foreign investment (in oil and infrastructure), increasing incomes and domestic demand, and growing retail and services spending. Nuri al-Maliki's national-unity government is weak and divided and may lose some members to the opposition, but it will stay in power. Americans will keep some boots on the ground if Mr al-Maliki suggests it. Economic progress will be slow, but the bounceback will keep growth at a very high rate.</p>

